  "description": "EDM meets tribal percussion — djembe and taiko trade kick duties while surdo provides the physical low-end surge. No beatbox, no synthetic sounds: the four-on-the-floor emerges from the physical drum bodies themselves. The GATHER macro builds from individual tribal voices to a complete primal ensemble drop. This is festival main stage energy from acoustic materials.",
